00:29:20.940 --> 00:29:33.470
So now I get to
compute what A(b) is.

00:29:33.470 --> 00:29:37.960
A(b) is the area under a curve.

00:29:37.960 --> 00:29:40.300
So it's going to be, let
me write it over here,

00:29:40.300 --> 00:29:47.160
A(b) is the area
under this curve here.

00:29:47.160 --> 00:29:51.580
Which is some constant
times-- so if you imagine,

00:29:51.580 --> 00:29:53.270
call this thing the name c.

00:29:53.270 --> 00:29:57.070
Under some curve, ce^(-x^2).

00:29:57.070 --> 00:29:59.040
Where the c is
equal to e^(-b^2).

00:30:06.380 --> 00:30:07.560
That's what our slice is.

00:30:07.560 --> 00:30:09.060
In fact, it looks
like one of those.

00:30:09.060 --> 00:30:12.970
It looks like one
of those bumps.

00:30:12.970 --> 00:30:14.630
Here's its formula again.

00:30:14.630 --> 00:30:17.850
It's the integral from
minus infinity to infinity

00:30:17.850 --> 00:30:19.500
of e^(-b^2) e^(-x^2) dx.

00:30:28.960 --> 00:30:31.560
We just recopied
what I had up there.

00:30:31.560 --> 00:30:37.430
And this is the height at
each value of x, with b fixed.

00:30:37.430 --> 00:30:42.630
And now, so we have
a lot of steps here.

00:30:42.630 --> 00:30:44.680
But each of them
is very elementary.

00:30:44.680 --> 00:30:47.380
The first one was just
that law of exponents.

00:30:47.380 --> 00:30:49.520
That we could split
the two into products.

00:30:49.520 --> 00:30:51.970
Now I'm going to make that
splitting even further.

00:30:51.970 --> 00:30:53.420
This is a constant.

00:30:53.420 --> 00:30:55.150
It's not varying with x.

00:30:55.150 --> 00:30:59.060
So I'm going to factor
it out of the integral.

00:30:59.060 --> 00:31:02.230
This is e^(-b^2) times the
integral from minus infinity

00:31:02.230 --> 00:31:03.850
to infinity of e^(-x^2) dx.

00:31:06.390 --> 00:31:09.890
So this might look frightening,
but actually it's just

00:31:09.890 --> 00:31:11.110
the property of an integral.

00:31:11.110 --> 00:31:13.180
All integrals have
this kind of property.

00:31:13.180 --> 00:31:17.090
You can always factor
out a constant.

00:31:17.090 --> 00:31:20.900
And now here comes
the remarkable thing.

00:31:20.900 --> 00:31:26.920
This is e^(-b^2) times a number
which is now familiar to us.

00:31:26.920 --> 00:31:27.980
What is this number?

00:31:27.980 --> 00:31:29.280
This is what we're looking for.

00:31:29.280 --> 00:31:40.550
This is our unknown, Q.
So I've computed A(b),

00:31:40.550 --> 00:31:44.260
and now I'm ready to
finish the problem off.

00:31:44.260 --> 00:31:48.720
A(b) = e^(-b^2) Q. Q is
that strange number which we

00:31:48.720 --> 00:31:49.380
don't know yet.

00:31:49.380 --> 00:31:51.850
What it is.

00:31:51.850 --> 00:31:55.570
So now I'm going to
compute the whole volume.

00:31:55.570 --> 00:31:57.850
The whole volume,
remember, it's over there,

00:31:57.850 --> 00:32:02.540
it's minus infinity
to infinity, A(y) dy.

00:32:02.540 --> 00:32:05.300
And now I'm just going to plug
in the formula that we've found

00:32:05.300 --> 00:32:07.860
for A. Now I'm doing
this for each b,

00:32:07.860 --> 00:32:09.740
so I'm doing it
varying over all b's.

00:32:09.740 --> 00:32:12.710
So I have the integral from
minus infinity to infinity.

00:32:12.710 --> 00:32:15.490
And here I have e^(-y^2).

00:32:15.490 --> 00:32:17.620
I've replaced b by y.

00:32:17.620 --> 00:32:21.640
And now I have Q. And I have dy.

00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:23.970
I just recopied what
I had over there

00:32:23.970 --> 00:32:27.100
into the formula for slicing.

00:32:27.100 --> 00:32:29.920
And now, I'm going to do
this trick of factoring out

00:32:29.920 --> 00:32:32.260
the constant a second time.

00:32:32.260 --> 00:32:33.860
This is a constant.

00:32:33.860 --> 00:32:35.180
It doesn't depend on y.

00:32:35.180 --> 00:32:38.030
It's the same for all y,
it just will factor out.

00:32:38.030 --> 00:32:40.880
So this is the same as Q
times the integral from minus

00:32:40.880 --> 00:32:47.350
infinity to infinity,
e^(-y^2) dy.

00:32:47.350 --> 00:32:52.200
And now, lo and behold,
this expression here.

00:32:52.200 --> 00:32:54.510
Of course, notice how
I defined Q. Let's

00:32:54.510 --> 00:32:56.950
go back carefully to
